A bit late on the new years post but I can truly say that 2022 has been by far the most testing/challenging, transformational & BEST year of my life. My husband, and I completed our first home renovation, sold everything we had, have lived in 3 different continents in a year and have traveled to places I’ve ever only dreamt of traveling to. I’m beyond grateful for the lessons and blessings that have come from this chapter. The most important lesson that I have learned is to love hard and be happy🥹💜 Your reality starts from the inside. #2022 #2023 #HappyNewYear

30 years around the sun!!😆🎂🎉🎈
It took me 30 years to realize that everything I have ever needed has always been within me. The key to happiness, peace and abundance is your ability to perceive that you are already those things. It’s not something outside of yourself. It took 30 years for me to return back to my playful childlike ways and wonder & to remember that this is the purist expression of self love. I let go of my traumas & the fears bestowed upon me by others. I am free and refuse to imprison my mind because I KNOW (Not believe) that I have the ability and power to do so.

I thank God for sending the people and experiences into my life that have allowed me to see past the illusions of fear, because on the other side of that I’ve found the promised land within. 🥹🙏🏽🌞🎂🎉🪅

The morning of delivery vs 8 weeks postpartum! This was by far the best pregnancy I’ve had. Many people don’t know this, but my entire pelvic floor prolapsed after baby number 4. I was in so much pain that my husband had to carry me up the stairs for 4 months straight after I gave birth. I did physical therapy & built up my strength to walk up the stairs again. Physical therapy was not enough to fix the problems so I got an intense surgery to put all my organs back in place. The healing process took a long 3 months. I changed my diet to vegan in the middle of my healing process because I felt like I was dying. It changed my life for the best.

During my first 4 pregnancies, I was extremely unhealthy. I had a terrible diet, kept getting infections, was in lots of pain, had many pregnancy complications & didn’t exercise at all. 

During this last pregnancy, even though I was vegan & was eating low inflammatory foods, I was a bit fearful of having another baby because I started having bad pains in my back & pelvic floor during the first few months. I didn’t want to prolapse again & didn’t want to have to go through another prolapse surgery so I did whatever I could to prevent it. I started mobility training, committing to 3 days a week up until the last 3 weeks of pregnancy. Just by changing my diet & incorporating full body exercise, I had NO pain, no cravings, no infections & didn’t need any medication the entire pregnancy! This showed me that I could have prevented my pelvic floor prolapse if I would have given my body the strength training & nutrients that it needed. I would have prevented the need to get my first C-section. (It’s a challenging recovery, but Im healing beautifully. Still taking things slow.) I hope all you soon to be moms out there learn from my story & really take care of yourself during pregnancy. I’m not saying to go vegan, but move your body & give it living foods. Stop giving it chemicals & fake food. Then sure enough, your body will respond the way you really need it to. This will play a large role in significantly raising the chances of preventing prolapse & or a C-section. Much love! ❤️🥰

Have you stopped to really ask yourself if those thoughts and things that you want are really YOUR thoughts & what YOU truly want? Or did someone place the idea in your head that made you think that you want certain things or even programmed you to believe in certain things? The moment you apply this question to everything in your life and start actually researching things and thinking for yourself, you will realize that most of what you have been programmed to believe & think, is a lie or just half true. Stop putting your trust into systems & people that make it seem like they have your best interest in mind. They want you to remain on autopilot so that they can benefit from your lack of true inner awareness. Stop making choices out of fear. God is not fear. Question everything. ❤️ Much love
-Amanda Harvey
